    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n::: narrow-section\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">7,730</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">14,103</div>\n<div style=\"display: block; &#10;              color: #ff6400; &#10;              font-size: 1.25em; &#10;              font-family: Graphik; &#10;              font-weight: bold; &#10;              text-align: center;\">NA</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Currently Eligible for<br>Parole but in Prison</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Eligible for Parole in<br>the next 1-5 years</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">\n<span class=\"tippy html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" height=\"338px\" id=\"htmlwidget-a68a31aa117a0c01aa6c\" width=\"100%\"></span>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-a68a31aa117a0c01aa6c\">{\"x\":{\"opts\":{\"placement\":\"bottom\",\"flip\":true,\"theme\":\"light\",\"content\":\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Moderately indeterminate<\\/b>: .\"},\"text\":\"<span aria-label=\\\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Moderately indeterminate<\\/b>: .\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" role=\\\"button\\\">Prison Sentencing<br>System&#9432;<\\/span>\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n<br>\n\n\n\n::: panel-tabset \n\n## Parole Eligibility\n\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">How is Parole Release Eligibility Determined?</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">When imposing a sentence of partial or total confinement, the court must impose a minimum and a maximum sentence. The court has discretion to set any maximum sentence within the statutory range, but the minimum term may not be greater than one-half the maximum selected by the court. Minimum sentences can be shorter than onehalf of the maximum term, in the court’s discretion, and  can be as short as one day. Inmates in state correctional facilities are eligible for parole release after the expiration of their minimum sentences.14 In practice, inmates are automatically scheduled for their parole hearing before their minimum eligibility date. The Board may not grant parole to inmates condemned to death, or sentenced to life imprisonment. At the time of sentencing, the court is required to aggregate all consecutive sentences and to indicate the aggregate minimum term to be served, which is not to exceed one half of the maximum aggregate term.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">People who are Eligible for Parole</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"bar-chart\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-e23b4e1b96b4ff2aeee7\" style=\"width:100%;height:454px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-e23b4e1b96b4ff2aeee7\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"width\":500,\"height\":350},\"title\":{\"text\":\"People who are Parole Eligible but Still in Prison by Race in 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":null},\"labels\":{\"enabled\":false}},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":false},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"ena